bastard
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:fellow, chap, joker, or as a term of address for a friend, esp. old bastard [As an informal term of both kindly and unkindly ref. and address without suggestion of illegitimacy more associated with Aust. than NZ, though as common here since the late 19c. as in that larger place: see AND: 1. of persons 1892; 2. of anything considered disagreeable or unpleasant 1919.]
