Quote:  Dan Freel's conversation was plentifully interlarded with oaths and obscenities that are - or would have been in the 80's - quite unprintable. At first it seemed an arresting, if not an interesting idiosyncracy, but one soon sickened of it. For instance he used the word bastard as the Americans use guy, and as we were then beginning to use bloke, to mean anyone about whom he was speaking ...
